Frontier Technology Inc. is looking for an experienced Business Analyst to support our work assessing Clients’ complex organizations to identify opportunities for improving organization performance and then monitoring their progress towards transformation. Your work with transformation can involve changes in process, information, guidance, organization structure, work management, learning, technology.
Your main tasks include reviewing Client information to establish their current state of operations, researching best practices, identifying and describing detailed requirements to enable the desired change, analyzing data to determine patterns and findings, creating and updating documentation to reflect the future state, and participating in the process of identifying and applying innovation. You will work with a wide variety of documentation types and other unstructured data from disparate sources to draw high value conclusions to support the delivery of successful change.
Frontier’s work is focused on identifying opportunities for organizational improvement and transformation across the organizations that are part of the Defense Healthcare Management Systems Program Executive Office (PEO DHMS). Our work applies the methodologies, data and decision support tool capabilities we developed under the Small Business Innovation Research (SBIR) program. Your work as part of our team will advance this unique set of capabilities in powerful new ways for the Military Health System and the Department of Defense as they deliver on the key objectives of Improved Readiness, Better Health, Better Care, and Lower Costs.

Review project information to understand the Client’s current operations and structure;
Collect, identify, define, and aggregate information for loading into analysis mechanisms;
Identify, define, categorize, and prioritize requirements that define the envisioned transformation;
Gain expertise with FTI proprietary tools and techniques and apply them in daily work;
Evaluate current business processes and uncover areas for potential improvement;
Apply best practices for enabling change with technology and developing the supporting requirements and documentation of envisioned solutions;
Manage the collection of compiled structured data and unstructured information/documentation to support discovery, reuse, and auditing;
